contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:38.371 --> 01:40.430
What was going on there, huh?

01:40.640 --> 01:42.540
We thought
you were sleeping, Daddy.

01:42.743 --> 01:46.008
How can I sleep with two
Twinkie burglars roaming around?

01:46.213 --> 01:48.078
<i>Can we watch
Dragon Tales, please?</i>

01:48.281 --> 01:50.875
Yeah. Why not, why not?

01:52.552 --> 01:54.417
Which one of these
turns on the TV?

02:09.568 --> 02:11.366
Honey, I think you
just opened the garage.

02:11.571 --> 02:13.368
I'm just planning ahead. I know.

02:14.975 --> 02:19.275
<i>- P-yew! Was that a stinky-dink bug?
- Good job.</i>

02:19.479 --> 02:21.242
Whatever happened
to the good old days...

02:21.448 --> 02:24.110
...when you pulled the knob
and on came the boob tube?

02:24.317 --> 02:26.979
The O'Doyles got
a universal remote control.

02:27.187 --> 02:29.246
One clicker controls everything.

02:29.456 --> 02:32.425
Makes life a lot easier
for old people like you.

02:33.360 --> 02:35.487
Well, whoop-de-do
for the O'Doyles.

02:35.695 --> 02:36.662
- Tree house?

02:36.863 --> 02:39.161
I don't know. Ask your father.

02:39.366 --> 02:40.628
Ask me what?

02:40.834 --> 02:44.565
Do you think you'll have time
to finish building the tree house ever?

02:44.771 --> 02:48.730
Yeah, Dad. It's kind of been
halfway done for two months now.

02:49.342 --> 02:54.177
All right. I want to, it's just I got a lot
of things going on at work right now.

02:54.381 --> 02:58.681
But as soon as I'm done, I'm on it.
I promise. Hang in there.

03:00.854 --> 03:04.346
Hey, look at Sundance
wrestle his duck.

03:05.158 --> 03:07.092
Oh, no, that's not wrestling.

03:07.294 --> 03:11.094
That's something you shouldn't
know about for another 10 to 30 years.

03:11.298 --> 03:13.528
Ten for you. Thirty for you.

03:16.937 --> 03:19.201
Hey, Michael? I'll see you tonight
at the swim meet?

03:19.406 --> 03:20.964
Swim meet.

03:22.042 --> 03:24.340
- I gotta go to that?
- Yes.

03:24.544 --> 03:28.674
- I'm kidding you. I'll be there. Okay?
- All right. I love you, Michael.

03:28.882 --> 03:31.009
Forever and ever, babe.

03:31.718 --> 03:32.980
Mr. Newman.

03:33.186 --> 03:35.211
Kevin O'Doyle.
Yeah. Always a pleasure.

03:35.422 --> 03:38.653
What kind of stereo you got
in that blue piece of shit?

03:38.859 --> 03:41.020
You know what?
I never checked, Kevin.

03:41.228 --> 03:43.662
Yeah, well, my father's stereo
is a Bose.

03:43.864 --> 03:46.662
Your father's stereo blows?
That's too bad.

03:46.867 --> 03:50.394
No! I said... That's not what I said!

03:50.604 --> 03:53.801
His father's stereo blows!

03:57.110 --> 03:59.738
Come on! Pay the man, let's go!

04:06.086 --> 04:08.145
- Good morning, Mr. Newman.
- Good morning.

04:08.355 --> 04:09.788
- Good morning, Mr. Newman.
- Hello.

04:09.990 --> 04:12.083
- Good morning, Mr. Newman.
- Hi.

04:13.093 --> 04:14.924
Good morning, Mr. Newman.

04:15.128 --> 04:16.789
- Good morning, Mr. Newman.
- Man, Alice...

04:16.997 --> 04:20.194
...I was stuck in traffic for an hour
and a half. When's the meeting?

04:21.401 --> 04:23.528
- It started already.
- What?

04:24.304 --> 04:25.566
Can I go to the bathroom?

04:25.772 --> 04:28.366
Go to the bathroom.
I told you, you don't have to ask me.

04:35.615 --> 04:37.640
Well, the interesting thing,
Prince Habeeboo...

04:37.851 --> 04:40.684
...is that the building codes
in Manhattan will allow us...

04:40.887 --> 04:42.878
- Michael.
- Sorry I'm late, sir.

04:43.089 --> 04:46.217
Some moron in a red Lamborghini
parked in my spot so...

04:46.426 --> 04:49.623
Prince Habeeboo
drive red Lamborghini.

04:50.497 --> 04:53.261
Red Lamborghini?
I meant blue Ferrari.

04:53.967 --> 04:56.231
Is this one of your partners?

04:56.436 --> 04:58.461
Actually, Michael
is just an associate.

04:58.672 --> 05:00.970
But he is one of our brightest
young architects.

05:01.174 --> 05:02.141
Thank you.

05:02.342 --> 05:04.367
Walk His Majesty
through our design concept.

05:04.577 --> 05:06.272
With pleasure.

05:07.080 --> 05:09.605
- Prince Haboobee...
- Habeeboo!

05:10.283 --> 05:12.308
Prince Habeeboo.

05:12.519 --> 05:15.010
Habeeboo. I thought I said that.

05:15.221 --> 05:17.883
When Mr. Ammer explained to me
the type of man you are...

05:18.091 --> 05:21.925
...a visionary who prides himself
on originality...

05:22.128 --> 05:26.929
...I said to myself, "Let's smash
the mold and redefine elegance."

05:27.133 --> 05:29.397
So I present to you your restaurant.

05:29.602 --> 05:31.092
Where is... Where's bar?

05:31.304 --> 05:34.967
Bar is... Here's the bar.
Now, the waterfall...

05:35.175 --> 05:36.233
Make bar longer.

05:37.677 --> 05:41.408
Okay. We could cut
into the atrium a little bit.

05:41.614 --> 05:46.142
No atrium. Just make bar longer
for Prince Habeeboo.

05:46.353 --> 05:47.320
Really?

05:49.489 --> 05:51.616
- Still itchy?
- You got it.

05:52.926 --> 05:56.191
And put big drain in floor
for wet T-shirt contest.

05:56.396 --> 05:57.920
Now, you're kidding me, right?

05:58.131 --> 06:00.156
Boob water's gotta
go someplace, Michael.

06:00.367 --> 06:03.734
Let's just take out the atrium and
run with that and there's your drain.

06:03.937 --> 06:07.429
- God.
- I love it. It is simply awesome.

06:08.008 --> 06:12.968
Yeah. Basically you want me to design
you an Arabian hoochie house?

06:13.179 --> 06:15.647
How dare you compare
Prince Habeeboo's Bikini Hut...

06:15.849 --> 06:17.783
...to this hoochie house?
- This idea's...

06:17.984 --> 06:20.350
...got nothing to do
with hoochies, Michael.

06:20.553 --> 06:22.043
It's like opposite of hoochie.

06:22.255 --> 06:24.052
No disrespect,
Prince Hubbida Hubbida.

06:24.257 --> 06:25.986
- Hubba Bubba.
- Habeeboo!

06:26.192 --> 06:29.286
Habeeboo!
Hubba Bubba is chewing gum.

06:29.496 --> 06:30.929
Prince Habeeboo's
not chewing gum.

06:31.131 --> 06:35.693
Prince Habeeboo, we will...
I will make this happen.

06:37.470 --> 06:38.437
John Ammer's office.

06:38.638 --> 06:41.607
I hope that atrium idea didn't take
too long to configure, Michael.

06:41.808 --> 06:44.572
Oh, there'll be other Junes
in my life, sir.

06:44.778 --> 06:49.340
See that parking garage
over there on 56?

06:49.649 --> 06:53.915
Watsuhita wants to knock it down
and build a luxury hotel.

06:54.120 --> 06:55.644
- You got the commission?
- Not yet.

06:55.855 --> 07:00.918
I just need someone to come up
with a design proposal. Intrigued?

07:02.829 --> 07:04.023
Hell, yes.

07:04.230 --> 07:07.358
I'm Fourth of July-ing with the kids.
When I get back, I'm all over it.

07:07.567 --> 07:11.936
Great. Have a great Fourth of July
with the kids. I'll put Swardson on it.

07:12.138 --> 07:15.938
No, no. Absolutely not.
L... l... Can't it just wait three days?

07:16.142 --> 07:18.940
These guys are Japanese.
They can't wait for their fish to cook.

07:21.514 --> 07:23.675
I guess I could talk to my wife.

07:23.883 --> 07:26.545
Great. See you later at happy hour
with Prince Habadabee.

07:27.220 --> 07:31.054
My son has a swim meet tonight
that I have to get to s...

07:31.257 --> 07:33.020
I'm just messing with you.
We're good.

07:38.231 --> 07:40.699
Yeah, Ben!

07:48.975 --> 07:53.571
That's my boy! That's my boy!
Kid, you were great!

07:54.013 --> 07:55.537
You're not my dad.

07:56.483 --> 07:59.145
- As far as you know.
- What?

08:00.520 --> 08:02.385
I was just joking.

08:02.589 --> 08:05.649
Is he really my dad?

08:05.859 --> 08:09.192
Come on, come on! Yes, Ben.
Yes, you did it!

08:09.395 --> 08:10.589
Honey, you were so great.

08:10.797 --> 08:14.255
Whoa, what are you, half a dolphin
or something? That was incredible.

08:14.467 --> 08:16.230
You just got here, Dad. I saw you.

08:17.337 --> 08:19.828
What do you mean I just got here?
Why are you saying that?

08:20.039 --> 08:22.007
I saw you. You jumped in there,
you swam here.

08:22.208 --> 08:25.803
- Then what stroke was he doing, Dad?
- He was doing the shut-up.

08:27.280 --> 08:30.681
Hey. Good thing is,
Daddy was here to see you finish.

08:30.884 --> 08:31.908
He didn't see me finish.

08:32.118 --> 08:34.347
He was hanging out
with Ping Woo for some reason.

08:34.554 --> 08:36.988
- Yeah, what was that about, huh?
- The kid was drowning.

08:37.190 --> 08:38.316
I'm gonna let him drown?

08:39.192 --> 08:40.818
Nobody goes drowning in my pool.

08:41.027 --> 08:43.587
How you doing? Bill Herlihy.
Ben's coach. You must be Dad.

08:43.796 --> 08:46.458
Michael Speedo...
Michael Newman. Sorry.

08:46.966 --> 08:49.628
Big Ben, that was great progress
out there, huh?

08:49.836 --> 08:52.669
Just remember, right arm out,
head turns left. Left arm out...

08:52.872 --> 08:55.500
Head turns right. I know.
I just forgot at the end.

08:55.708 --> 08:56.732
Well, that's all right.

08:56.943 --> 09:00.242
You master that, people are gonna
think you're a half a dolphin out there.

09:00.446 --> 09:02.505
- Really?
- Yeah.

09:03.383 --> 09:04.782
Cute.

09:05.451 --> 09:07.612
Hello? Mr. Ammer.

09:15.728 --> 09:18.492
Ben, honey, slow down.
It's not a race.

09:18.698 --> 09:20.393
That's his second one
in five minutes.

09:20.600 --> 09:22.295
Keeps eating more and more.

09:22.502 --> 09:25.403
He's like a machine.
He can't still be hungry.

09:25.605 --> 09:29.097
He's not. He's just doing whatever
Michael's doing. It's driving me crazy.

09:29.309 --> 09:32.972
Everything Michael's been doing lately
is very unhealthy for him.

09:33.179 --> 09:35.545
He's gonna kill himself.

09:36.316 --> 09:38.910
Like a signature building
we're talking about.

09:39.118 --> 09:40.517
Oh, my God.

09:42.355 --> 09:43.913
Scared the crap out of me.

09:44.524 --> 09:46.890
Dad, how much longer
are you gonna live?

09:47.894 --> 09:50.488
- One minute.
- One minute?

09:50.697 --> 09:52.790
- Daddy's gonna die in one minute!
- Oh, no, honey.

09:52.999 --> 09:54.364
Don't worry. I'm not dying.

09:54.567 --> 09:58.435
I'm gonna live for 200 years.
Is that long enough for you and me?

09:59.005 --> 10:02.736
- Promise?
- I promise. Swear. Come here.

10:04.077 --> 10:05.704
You son of a bitch!

10:05.912 --> 10:08.676
Hey! There are families here!

10:08.881 --> 10:11.213
Show some respect,
you pieces of shit!

10:11.951 --> 10:14.715
Go home and watch VH1, old man.

10:14.921 --> 10:17.754
Don't light another damn one!

10:19.058 --> 10:21.583
Benjamin. Benjamin.
What am I holding?

10:21.794 --> 10:24.592
A quarter. Now, Grandma
does not let me eat ice cream...

10:24.797 --> 10:26.389
...because of my diabetes.
- True.

10:26.599 --> 10:30.262
But she says nothing, however,
about a tasty quarter.

10:30.703 --> 10:31.965
Okay.

10:34.173 --> 10:35.765
All right. All right.

10:35.975 --> 10:39.706
Very quickly, please, count to three
because it tastes terrible.

10:39.912 --> 10:43.245
One, two, three.

10:44.884 --> 10:46.511
Are you shitting me?

10:46.719 --> 10:49.483
First he's eating like his father,
now you're talking like him?

10:49.689 --> 10:52.055
- Ben.
- Don't you ever say that again.

10:52.258 --> 10:55.591
- Sorry, Grandma.
- How do you do that, Grandpa?

10:55.962 --> 10:58.658
A good magician
never reveals his secrets.

10:58.865 --> 11:01.459
Your daddy has wanted to know
how I've done that trick...

11:01.668 --> 11:02.794
...since he was your age.

11:03.002 --> 11:04.401
Isn't that true, son?

11:04.604 --> 11:06.936
Hey, Michael.
Michael, who are you talking to?

11:07.140 --> 11:10.132
Jesus. I'm talking to my boss, Ma.
Take it easy.

11:10.343 --> 11:12.004
Oh, yeah?
Well, tell him to get a life.

11:12.211 --> 11:14.441
You got family here.
You're busy. Come on.

11:14.647 --> 11:15.978
My mother says hello.

11:16.182 --> 11:18.412
Oh, he's such a big boy, isn't he?

11:18.618 --> 11:21.951
On his big cell phone. Big boy.

11:22.155 --> 11:27.491
That's it. Get some sleep. Thank you,
Mr. Ammer. All right. Good night.

11:27.694 --> 11:30.128
- Are you done? Can we relax now?
- Sorry.

11:31.764 --> 11:34.198
Eat me, grandpa!

11:34.634 --> 11:35.692
You're dead.

11:36.369 --> 11:39.634
- Oh, shit!
- Yeah, you better run!

11:39.839 --> 11:41.636
I kicked your father's ass
in high school!

11:41.841 --> 11:43.172
Now I'm gonna kick yours!

11:43.376 --> 11:46.106
I hate that man.

11:46.412 --> 11:48.539
Okay, good night, you two cowboys.

11:48.748 --> 11:51.239
- Reach for the sky, Pocahontas.
- No, back to bed.

11:51.451 --> 11:55.046
Come on. Pocahontas is off duty.
I'm out of here.

11:58.024 --> 12:00.219
You getting sick, sheriff?

12:00.660 --> 12:02.719
I don't got time to be sick, so no.

12:02.929 --> 12:05.796
I need to watch this documentary
on Asian architecture.

12:05.998 --> 12:08.728
Well, you gotta get some rest
sometime, sweetheart.

12:08.935 --> 12:11.199
Besides, the woodland creatures
will laugh at you...

12:11.404 --> 12:13.998
...if you collapse trying
to put up the tent this weekend.

12:15.108 --> 12:18.635
Yeah. I forgot to tell you.

12:19.078 --> 12:21.171
We gotta postpone
the camping trip.

12:21.881 --> 12:23.746
Ammer put me on a project.

12:23.950 --> 12:26.350
It's due Tuesday. If I don't finish,
I'm off it, so...

12:26.552 --> 12:28.713
The kids have been talking
about camping all year.

12:28.921 --> 12:30.013
Think I don't know that?

12:30.223 --> 12:32.487
It's just every choice I make,
everything I do...

12:32.692 --> 12:34.592
...I disappoint somebody.

12:34.794 --> 12:37.388
Make sure you don't keep
disappointing the wrong people.

12:37.597 --> 12:40.122
I'm not out drinking or gambling
or hitting on chicks.

12:40.333 --> 12:43.097
I'm working my ass off
so my family can have a better life...

12:43.302 --> 12:45.065
...than I dreamed of
when I was a kid.

12:45.605 --> 12:49.200
The only way for that to happen
is for me to watch this stinking show!

12:49.409 --> 12:51.240
So relax, hon.

12:54.781 --> 12:56.271
Are you kidding me?

12:56.482 --> 12:59.508
Will you give me a break one time?

12:59.986 --> 13:03.547
Damn it! The O'Doyles got
a stinking universal remote control.

13:03.756 --> 13:05.587
We're gonna have one too.

13:05.792 --> 13:07.555
I'm sick of this.

13:12.165 --> 13:14.633
You want me to open
the garage for you?

13:27.613 --> 13:28.580
Closed.

13:31.317 --> 13:32.284
Closed.

13:34.120 --> 13:35.087
Open.

13:35.288 --> 13:37.620
Bed Bath & Beyond it is.

13:42.995 --> 13:44.622
Hey, man?

13:44.831 --> 13:47.766
You guys got any universal
remote controls in there?

13:47.967 --> 13:50.834
- For a shower curtain or a bathmat?
- For a television.

13:51.671 --> 13:53.969
I don't think so.
Maybe for a blanket?

13:54.173 --> 13:55.765
You got a remote for a blanket?

13:56.509 --> 13:58.943
Sorry, I don't work here.
I'm waiting for my friends.

13:59.145 --> 14:00.510
You're kidding me.

14:00.713 --> 14:03.739
Actually, yes. I don't have any friends.
Will you be my friend?

14:07.887 --> 14:09.514
Wow, man.

14:12.492 --> 14:15.256
Bed. Bed.

14:15.461 --> 14:18.225
Bath. Bath.

14:18.431 --> 14:20.126
Bed.

14:22.301 --> 14:24.963
So tired of my life.

14:30.676 --> 14:31.870
Beyond?

15:08.915 --> 15:10.746
Sorry to sneak up on you. I just...

15:10.950 --> 15:13.248
You guys got a universal
remote control back here?

15:15.621 --> 15:18.886
Something stinks
like stale french fries.

15:20.259 --> 15:22.227
All right, that's probably me.

15:22.428 --> 15:25.226
You know, fast food
shortens your life.

15:25.431 --> 15:26.659
Yeah, that's what I heard.

15:26.866 --> 15:30.029
But the way my life's been going
lately, that ain't such a bad thing.

15:30.236 --> 15:32.397
You're looking
for a universal remote control?

15:32.605 --> 15:35.039
Yeah. Just one device
to do it all for me...

15:35.241 --> 15:39.371
...make my life a little easier,
quicker, not so damn complicated.

15:39.579 --> 15:43.015
I'm not supposed to do this,
but you seem like a good guy.

15:43.215 --> 15:44.842
Hey. Somebody noticed. Thank you.

15:45.051 --> 15:47.110
I'm gonna show you a remote
we just got in...

15:47.320 --> 15:49.880
...that's probably the most advanced
piece of technology...

15:50.089 --> 15:51.181
...we have in this place.

15:51.557 --> 15:54.287
- Sounds sweet.
- It is sweet.

15:54.493 --> 15:59.123
The latest, greatest universal remote
not even on the market yet.

15:59.332 --> 16:04.065
I guess the O'Doyles' remote can bite
my advanced-technological ass then.

16:04.270 --> 16:06.761
I don't know the O'Doyles...

16:07.974 --> 16:09.635
...but they can bite it hard.

16:09.842 --> 16:11.207
Yeah.

16:11.410 --> 16:12.809
Come in the back with me.

16:13.312 --> 16:14.836
Okay.

16:15.815 --> 16:18.045
This is... This is very nice of you.

16:18.517 --> 16:21.384
- What's your name, anyways?
- Call me Morty.

16:21.587 --> 16:22.884
Morty, I'm Michael Newman.

16:23.289 --> 16:25.348
Michael Newman.

16:27.193 --> 16:29.093
I'm about to rock your world.

16:29.528 --> 16:30.722
Okay.

16:40.072 --> 16:43.872
I gotta be honest with you. This place
looks bigger from the outside.

16:44.076 --> 16:45.839
Just kidding.

16:47.246 --> 16:48.611
Hey, hey.

17:07.733 --> 17:09.530
I think maybe there in the middle?

17:22.647 --> 17:24.616
Sneaky.

17:29.889 --> 17:32.119
Where's the box?
Does it come with directions?

17:32.324 --> 17:33.848
Not necessary.

17:34.060 --> 17:37.621
Just point, click.

17:37.830 --> 17:39.957
Eventually, it will program itself.

17:42.868 --> 17:43.857
How much is this thing?

17:44.070 --> 17:46.561
Because I ain't exactly
Thurston Howell, you know?

17:46.772 --> 17:50.071
Lucky for you, it's not
in the bar-code system yet.

17:50.276 --> 17:53.541
So I'm gonna have
to just give it to you.

17:53.746 --> 17:56.180
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
What's the catch here, man?

17:56.382 --> 17:59.818
Want me to take my shirt off for you?
Because I don't play for that team.

18:00.019 --> 18:02.715
Hey. Man, get out of here.

18:03.556 --> 18:04.887
Why are you doing this, then?

18:05.091 --> 18:08.822
Because good guys need a break
every once in a while.

18:09.829 --> 18:11.023
Take it.

18:11.864 --> 18:12.831
Enjoy.

18:15.768 --> 18:16.996
All right.

18:17.203 --> 18:19.501
Only one thing
you need to know, Michael.

18:19.705 --> 18:22.367
This item is nonreturnable.

18:22.575 --> 18:26.102
Why would I wanna return something
I got for free?

18:47.500 --> 18:50.367
Twinkie. You don't need it.
You don't need it, man.

18:50.569 --> 18:53.868
You do need a Yodel, though.
Okay. Good job.

18:54.373 --> 18:56.898
Let's see what you got, mate.

19:04.350 --> 19:08.616
Look at me, turning my own TV on.
I'm a freaking whiz kid.

19:09.755 --> 19:11.655
<i>- Residential architecture...</i>

19:11.857 --> 19:13.722
- So I talked to the kids.
- Oh, yeah?

19:13.926 --> 19:16.759
They're very understanding about
not going camping this weekend.

19:16.962 --> 19:19.726
- Great.
- They could have a sleepover instead.

19:19.932 --> 19:22.196
That's a great idea.
Thank you, thank you.

19:22.401 --> 19:25.029
Thanks for being
so cool about this too.

19:25.237 --> 19:27.671
- Can I ask you something?
- Yes.

19:27.873 --> 19:31.832
After you do all this work and become
a big player at your company...

19:32.044 --> 19:34.342
...do you think you're gonna
have more time for us...

