01:14:51.160 --> 01:14:52.593
I have cancer?

01:14:52.795 --> 01:14:54.626
No, you had cancer.

01:14:54.830 --> 01:14:57.060
You're the only person
to gain weight during chemo.

01:14:57.266 --> 01:14:59.257
That's probably what caused
your heart attack.

01:14:59.468 --> 01:15:00.730
Heart attack?

01:15:00.936 --> 01:15:02.927
I thought they weaned you
off the morphine.

01:15:03.672 --> 01:15:05.299
Okay, Mr. Junk Food...

01:15:05.508 --> 01:15:08.102
...since the injury,
you haven't been healthy a full day.

01:15:08.310 --> 01:15:10.676
When exactly did I hurt my head?

01:15:11.647 --> 01:15:15.014
When was it? Like, six years ago?

01:15:15.217 --> 01:15:20.587
Six more years! No! No!
It skipped all my sickness.

01:15:20.789 --> 01:15:22.757
I'm gonna ask them
to cut back on painkillers.

01:15:22.958 --> 01:15:24.516
Donna, don't go.

01:15:26.195 --> 01:15:27.856
What's this?

01:15:30.399 --> 01:15:34.426
That's not bad
for your third liposuction.

01:15:35.671 --> 01:15:37.536
One more tummy tuck
should take care of it.

01:15:38.607 --> 01:15:41.337
Oh, it looks like a tongue...

01:15:41.544 --> 01:15:43.136
...licking.

01:15:44.246 --> 01:15:47.704
Look, I should go.
Bill's waiting for me downstairs.

01:15:47.917 --> 01:15:49.817
- So I'll probably...
- Bill?

01:15:50.019 --> 01:15:52.385
You're still with Speedo Torpedo?

01:15:52.588 --> 01:15:55.216
Whatever happened
to "forever and ever," honey?

01:15:55.424 --> 01:15:57.551
"Forever and ever"?

01:15:57.760 --> 01:16:01.093
Look, Michael, I'm trying to have
a civilized relationship with you...

01:16:01.297 --> 01:16:02.628
...for the kids' sake.

01:16:02.831 --> 01:16:05.459
I really wanna be friends,
but I can't do that if you...

01:16:05.668 --> 01:16:07.329
Would you stop flapping that thing?

01:16:07.536 --> 01:16:10.300
It's my flap, I'll do
whatever the hell I want with it!

01:16:12.208 --> 01:16:13.232
You done?

01:16:15.211 --> 01:16:17.372
Look, Bill's my husband.

01:16:17.580 --> 01:16:20.378
Please learn to accept that.
I really have to go.

01:16:20.583 --> 01:16:22.915
Husband? Donna?

01:16:23.118 --> 01:16:28.715
No. Donna. Donna. Donna!

01:16:29.291 --> 01:16:31.953
<i>Welcome to Newman Architecture.</i>

01:16:32.161 --> 01:16:34.789
<i>Building a better world for all of us.</i>

01:16:34.997 --> 01:16:37.158
<i>Architect of the year, 2018.</i>

01:16:37.366 --> 01:16:39.891
All your dreams came true,
huh, moron?

01:16:40.102 --> 01:16:42.935
Dad. Hey, how you feeling?

01:16:44.840 --> 01:16:48.503
- Benjamin. Look at that.
- Look... What?

01:16:48.711 --> 01:16:52.875
Your face. Your skinny face.
You're shaving now, huh, kid?

01:16:53.082 --> 01:16:57.610
Your entire ass is gone.
What happened? Good for you.

01:16:57.820 --> 01:17:02.257
Right, my ass. Why don't
we talk about it in my office.

01:17:05.094 --> 01:17:07.255
My old office.

01:17:10.499 --> 01:17:13.696
The architect. How did this happen?

01:17:13.902 --> 01:17:17.963
- Mom said you were still a little loopy.
- No, no, no. I'm feeling terrific.

01:17:18.173 --> 01:17:21.768
The weight. How did you do it?
Staple treatment like your old man?

01:17:21.977 --> 01:17:24.036
Wanna have a flap fight?
You gotta see this...

01:17:24.246 --> 01:17:27.738
No. Just working out with Bill
five times a week. Same as always.

01:17:33.055 --> 01:17:38.357
That's a looker.
Blondie, big lips. Chesty.

01:17:38.560 --> 01:17:39.788
Is that your girl?

01:17:40.596 --> 01:17:42.621
No, that's your daughter Samantha.

01:17:43.065 --> 01:17:44.498
Of course it is.

01:17:44.700 --> 01:17:47.328
And you better
always take care of her...

01:17:47.536 --> 01:17:51.336
...and make sure nobody touches her
except you.

01:17:52.274 --> 01:17:55.402
Pop, I'm just getting ready
for this meeting.

01:17:56.812 --> 01:17:59.838
Okay. Absolutely.
I'll take off for you.

01:18:01.784 --> 01:18:05.652
I'd like to spend more time together.
All of us.

01:18:05.854 --> 01:18:07.913
Take you out for ice cream.
How's that?

01:18:08.290 --> 01:18:10.155
I know your mother won't come...

01:18:10.359 --> 01:18:14.489
...but you, Samantha,
Grandpa, Grandma.

01:18:14.897 --> 01:18:16.194
That'd be nice, huh?

01:18:17.833 --> 01:18:20.267
I knew something
was funny with you today.

01:18:20.469 --> 01:18:23.996
Papa, take a seat.
Let me get you a water, okay?

01:18:25.341 --> 01:18:27.468
What are we sitting for?

01:18:28.711 --> 01:18:32.647
- Here you go, Pop, drink this.
- All right. Drink some water.

01:18:34.650 --> 01:18:36.447
There, I had my water.
What's going on?

01:18:39.755 --> 01:18:41.518
Grandpa died, Dad.

01:18:44.660 --> 01:18:46.890
He died a while back now.

01:18:51.333 --> 01:18:55.394
No, no, no.

01:18:55.604 --> 01:18:57.970
Don't say that.

01:18:58.774 --> 01:19:01.504
Where was I?

01:19:01.710 --> 01:19:03.007
You're crying?

01:19:04.113 --> 01:19:06.206
What happened?

01:19:07.249 --> 01:19:11.913
Nothing. You know,
he just got old. That's life.

01:19:12.121 --> 01:19:15.989
- Shit.
- You're born and you live and you die.

01:19:17.326 --> 01:19:18.623
Man, I gotta go.

01:19:18.827 --> 01:19:20.954
Hey, hang on.
Susie, push my next meeting.

01:19:21.163 --> 01:19:23.427
No, no, do your meeting.
It's fine. I'm just dizzy.

01:19:23.632 --> 01:19:26.362
- Why are you crying?
- I'm dizzy from the operation.

01:19:26.568 --> 01:19:30.231
- You're gonna make me cry, Dad.
- You don't... You don't have to go.

01:19:34.476 --> 01:19:36.740
You look... You look good.

01:19:36.945 --> 01:19:38.845
It's all right. Goodbye.

01:19:53.996 --> 01:19:55.657
Come on.

01:19:55.864 --> 01:19:57.195
Come on.

01:19:57.399 --> 01:19:59.458
It won't take you there.

01:20:00.002 --> 01:20:01.469
Take me where?

01:20:02.237 --> 01:20:05.070
To the moment he died.
You weren't there.

01:20:05.474 --> 01:20:07.533
Of course I wasn't.

01:20:09.278 --> 01:20:11.610
Can you take me
to the last time I saw him, please?

01:20:15.217 --> 01:20:18.744
Hey, Dad. Sorry to bug you.

01:20:18.954 --> 01:20:22.321
Would you mind looking
at my shopping mall design again?

01:20:22.524 --> 01:20:23.786
This one is cheaper.

01:20:23.992 --> 01:20:27.018
But if you check this out...

01:20:27.229 --> 01:20:30.255
...you'll see it has
a much better natural flow...

01:20:30.466 --> 01:20:33.492
Cheaper one, like I said.
Now, just let me do my e-mail.

01:20:35.471 --> 01:20:37.564
Yeah. Yeah, you're right, Dad.

01:20:37.773 --> 01:20:40.742
He ain't right. You're a schmuck!
Look at it!

01:20:41.276 --> 01:20:42.265
Surprise.

01:20:42.478 --> 01:20:44.810
Hey, Grandpa.

01:20:45.247 --> 01:20:47.772
Oh, my God.

01:20:51.587 --> 01:20:54.078
When did you get so handsome?

01:20:54.289 --> 01:20:56.689
So, Michael, I had a wonderful idea.

01:20:56.892 --> 01:20:59.292
Your mother's playing canasta
with her friends tonight.

01:20:59.495 --> 01:21:01.861
I thought,
"What a great opportunity."

01:21:02.064 --> 01:21:05.124
You, me and Ben should go
and have a boys' night out.

01:21:05.334 --> 01:21:07.768
- Can't.
- What do you mean you can't?

01:21:07.970 --> 01:21:09.130
You have to eat sometime.

01:21:09.338 --> 01:21:11.738
We could go,
we could whistle at pretty girls.

01:21:11.940 --> 01:21:14.204
- I'm down for that.
- See? He's down.

01:21:14.409 --> 01:21:16.468
I don't know what it means,
but he's down.

01:21:16.678 --> 01:21:20.114
- Hey. Please.
- Don't give me that finger.

01:21:25.153 --> 01:21:27.280
I'll make you a deal.

01:21:27.489 --> 01:21:31.823
If you come, I'll show you
the quarter trick.

01:21:32.027 --> 01:21:34.393
- Will you look at the man?
- I'll tell you the secret.

01:21:34.596 --> 01:21:36.496
No, Dad.

01:21:36.698 --> 01:21:37.960
Don't you wanna know how l...?

01:21:38.166 --> 01:21:40.634
I know how you do the stupid trick.
I've always known.

01:21:40.836 --> 01:21:42.133
Can you let me do my work?

01:21:46.708 --> 01:21:48.369
You've always known.

01:21:48.577 --> 01:21:50.044
You're pathetic.

01:21:51.046 --> 01:21:52.570
Okay.

01:21:55.250 --> 01:21:57.810
I'm so sorry I barged in.

01:21:58.220 --> 01:22:00.313
I love you, son.

01:22:03.125 --> 01:22:04.990
See you later, Grandpa, I love you.

01:22:05.193 --> 01:22:06.785
Dad.

01:22:07.462 --> 01:22:09.225
Pop.

01:22:09.431 --> 01:22:11.126
Pop.

01:22:35.190 --> 01:22:37.249
I love you, son.

01:22:41.263 --> 01:22:43.322
I love you, son.

01:22:45.033 --> 01:22:47.058
I love you, son.

01:22:53.041 --> 01:22:55.236
I love you too, Dad.

01:23:00.515 --> 01:23:02.312
I'll miss you.

01:23:04.686 --> 01:23:06.051
You know that.

01:23:09.725 --> 01:23:11.386
Goodbye.

01:23:37.219 --> 01:23:39.585
I'm sorry about your father.

01:23:40.022 --> 01:23:43.981
Taking him wasn't something
I wanted to do.

01:23:44.726 --> 01:23:46.159
What do you mean "taking him"?

01:23:46.361 --> 01:23:47.953
I'm an angel, Michael.

01:23:48.497 --> 01:23:50.158
An angel?

01:23:51.066 --> 01:23:53.591
I thought an angel was
supposed to protect people.

01:23:53.802 --> 01:23:55.861
I'm the angel of death.

01:23:57.806 --> 01:24:00.604
Your dad, it was his time.

01:24:02.210 --> 01:24:04.178
You bastard.

01:24:11.920 --> 01:24:13.785
All right, leave me alone.
Leave me alone.

01:24:13.989 --> 01:24:17.447
You had your fun.
Just take me to a good place.

01:24:33.442 --> 01:24:38.038
And now, everybody, it's time
for Mr. Newman to say a few words.

01:24:38.647 --> 01:24:40.205
Yay, Michael!

01:24:42.250 --> 01:24:45.014
Go get them, Michael! Speech!

01:24:47.823 --> 01:24:50.314
Wedding cake. Wedding cake.

01:24:51.093 --> 01:24:53.891
Okay, where's the groom?
Show your face.

01:24:54.096 --> 01:24:55.688
Hi, Dad.

01:24:56.398 --> 01:25:00.027
Ben. I didn't miss
my son's wedding.

01:25:00.235 --> 01:25:04.672
Wow, this is terrific, buddy.
Who's the lucky lady?

01:25:05.307 --> 01:25:07.901
Very funny, Mr. Newman.

01:25:10.779 --> 01:25:12.246
Aunt Peggy, is that you?

01:25:13.815 --> 01:25:15.749
God, you got old.

01:25:17.719 --> 01:25:23.055
No, no. L... She... I'm just playing.
She knows that.

01:25:28.897 --> 01:25:30.194
Ma.

01:25:34.302 --> 01:25:36.702
Ben's wife...

01:25:37.339 --> 01:25:38.601
...welcome to the family.

01:25:38.807 --> 01:25:39.967
Thank you.

01:25:40.175 --> 01:25:42.973
Congratulations.
Let's have the best night, okay?

01:25:52.954 --> 01:25:57.550
Look at you, Ma. You look amazing.

01:25:59.227 --> 01:26:02.890
Michael, you haven't kissed me
like that since you were a little boy.

01:26:03.098 --> 01:26:06.431
You are the best, Ma.
You know I know that, right?

01:26:06.635 --> 01:26:09.798
Oh, darling, that's so sweet.

01:26:10.472 --> 01:26:14.272
You know, Michael, your father
would've loved to be here.

01:26:14.476 --> 01:26:15.943
I know, Ma.

01:26:16.812 --> 01:26:19.838
Okay? I'm just glad you're here.

01:26:20.615 --> 01:26:25.985
Me too, bubbala. Me too. Me too.
It's beautiful. Beautiful.

01:26:26.454 --> 01:26:27.819
Beautiful. Look at her.

01:26:28.490 --> 01:26:30.481
Donna, my favorite.

01:26:31.326 --> 01:26:33.658
You're such a schmuck
for letting her go.

01:26:33.862 --> 01:26:36.956
But don't let me ruin your evening.
I'll talk to you later.

01:26:37.165 --> 01:26:39.133
Christina.

01:26:41.937 --> 01:26:44.770
Michael, you've been so generous
taking care of all this...

01:26:44.973 --> 01:26:46.133
...and the kids' honeymoon.

01:26:46.341 --> 01:26:48.434
- Absolutely.
- Thank you so much.

01:26:48.643 --> 01:26:52.841
Of course. Ben's wife
seems like a nice kid, huh?

01:26:53.048 --> 01:26:55.983
- I think she's wonderful.
- Definite keeper.

01:26:56.184 --> 01:26:59.711
Here's one you might remember
from The Cranberries.

01:27:05.060 --> 01:27:07.654
Out of all the songs, huh?

01:27:09.297 --> 01:27:11.231
Bill, since it's our son's wedding...

01:27:11.433 --> 01:27:14.334
...do you mind if I dance
with my ex-husband for a minute?

01:27:14.536 --> 01:27:16.800
- Not at all.
- Thank you.

01:27:17.005 --> 01:27:19.565
Just have her back by midnight,
all right, champ?

01:27:19.774 --> 01:27:20.968
You got it, Bill.

01:27:33.221 --> 01:27:35.587
Why does he have
a bathing suit on?

01:27:37.292 --> 01:27:39.453
Nice Speedo, buddy.

01:27:51.473 --> 01:27:53.338
Still smelling good, huh?

01:27:53.541 --> 01:27:56.032
After all these years.

01:27:57.746 --> 01:27:59.213
Are you happy?

01:27:59.414 --> 01:28:02.144
Of course I'm happy,
our son just got married.

01:28:02.350 --> 01:28:07.014
Not about that. Are you happy
about where our lives ended up?

01:28:07.222 --> 01:28:10.089
"Ended." It's not over yet.

01:28:10.292 --> 01:28:13.955
- That's my Donna.
- It's true.

01:28:15.463 --> 01:28:17.090
That Samantha?

01:28:17.699 --> 01:28:22.033
Hey. What are you doing?
Put a sweater on. Cover them up.

01:28:23.038 --> 01:28:24.437
What is with you?

01:28:26.408 --> 01:28:28.273
Just kidding, I...

01:28:28.476 --> 01:28:31.309
Just not used to seeing you
all grown-up like this.

01:28:32.314 --> 01:28:37.251
Okay, well, if that's your way of telling
me that I look pretty, then thank you.

01:28:37.786 --> 01:28:39.219
Let's go get some cake.

01:28:39.421 --> 01:28:41.321
- I'll race you there, Dad. Come on.
- Okay.

01:28:43.024 --> 01:28:44.651
"Dad"?

01:28:47.162 --> 01:28:48.459
Michael, are you okay?

01:28:51.066 --> 01:28:54.593
Is there a doctor?
We need a doctor here!

01:28:57.706 --> 01:28:59.003
Michael!

01:28:59.207 --> 01:29:01.971
- Dad!
- Dad!

01:29:03.979 --> 01:29:05.674
It's just corn flakes.

01:29:31.006 --> 01:29:33.770
One dance, you pop an artery.

01:29:35.043 --> 01:29:39.173
Why'd you make me
waste my entire life?

01:29:39.381 --> 01:29:41.474
You were fast-forwarding
through your life...

01:29:41.683 --> 01:29:44.049
...long before you ever met me.

01:29:44.252 --> 01:29:46.311
You lived the life you chose,
big shot.

01:29:47.188 --> 01:29:49.281
This is not the life I wanted.

01:29:49.491 --> 01:29:50.890
It is.

01:29:56.131 --> 01:29:57.325
Looks like it is.

01:30:01.202 --> 01:30:04.330
Hey. You're up. How you feeling?

01:30:06.274 --> 01:30:09.209
I feel better
now that you guys are here.

01:30:09.411 --> 01:30:11.675
Samantha's been here
like 36 hours straight.

01:30:11.880 --> 01:30:15.247
She said she wouldn't leave
the hospital until you woke up.

01:30:16.217 --> 01:30:20.244
- Why'd you do that?
- Because. You're my father.

01:30:20.855 --> 01:30:23.323
I thought Bill was your father.

01:30:24.059 --> 01:30:26.186
I have two fathers.

01:30:27.162 --> 01:30:31.826
One of them told me he was gonna
live till he was 200. Remember?

01:30:33.735 --> 01:30:36.169
You both really need
to get some sleep.

01:30:36.371 --> 01:30:38.566
And I got a plane to catch.

01:30:39.307 --> 01:30:42.003
Big Ben's gotta go
on his honeymoon.

01:30:42.677 --> 01:30:45.271
Actually, I just canceled
the honeymoon.

01:30:45.480 --> 01:30:49.348
Kensington deal might fall through,
so I gotta go do damage control.

01:30:49.551 --> 01:30:51.348
- Julie and I can go to Italy anytime.
- No.

01:30:51.553 --> 01:30:52.781
It's not that big a deal.

01:30:52.987 --> 01:30:55.217
- That's not fair to your wife.
- Dad...

01:30:55.423 --> 01:30:58.358
...she gets it. Keeping
the business going is more important.

01:30:58.560 --> 01:31:01.324
Guys, I'm sorry. You're gonna
have to leave. He needs his rest.

01:31:01.529 --> 01:31:02.689
All right. Bye, Dad.

01:31:03.998 --> 01:31:05.761
Bye, Daddy.

01:31:17.212 --> 01:31:18.975
Get this off of me.

01:31:23.518 --> 01:31:25.247
Whoa, whoa!

01:31:25.453 --> 01:31:27.978
Hey, fella, you're a long way
from walking out of here.

01:31:28.189 --> 01:31:29.656
I gotta see my son.

01:31:29.858 --> 01:31:32.258
You're not going anywhere.
Now, get back into the bed.

01:31:33.027 --> 01:31:35.086
- Isn't that Colin Farrell?
- Where?

01:31:41.169 --> 01:31:42.534
Michael.

01:31:42.737 --> 01:31:46.173
Those machines
are keeping you alive.

01:31:46.374 --> 01:31:48.842
I gotta talk to my boy.

01:31:55.783 --> 01:31:58.013
- Michael, stop.
- No.

01:32:00.755 --> 01:32:03.747
Michael, it doesn't have to end now.

01:32:12.400 --> 01:32:14.334
Ben!

01:32:26.481 --> 01:32:27.675
Ben!

01:32:36.424 --> 01:32:39.222
Ben!

01:32:41.162 --> 01:32:44.563
Ben!

01:32:47.101 --> 01:32:49.160
Dad? Dad?

01:32:49.737 --> 01:32:51.728
Dad, what are you doing?

01:32:51.940 --> 01:32:54.067
Are you okay?

01:32:54.776 --> 01:32:58.337
- Oh, my God.
- Help! Help!

01:32:58.546 --> 01:33:00.537
- Dad! Dad!
- Help!

01:33:00.748 --> 01:33:02.306
Ben, Ben.

01:33:06.387 --> 01:33:09.151
Family. Family. Family.

01:33:09.357 --> 01:33:10.415
What?

01:33:10.625 --> 01:33:14.994
Family. Family. Family comes first.

01:33:15.563 --> 01:33:17.258
Family comes first.

01:33:17.465 --> 01:33:19.592
Honeymoon. Honeymoon.

01:33:20.068 --> 01:33:23.231
Honeymoon. I love you.

01:33:25.039 --> 01:33:27.564
Samantha. Samantha.

01:33:27.775 --> 01:33:32.075
I didn't make 200, but I love you.

01:33:32.280 --> 01:33:34.111
I love you.

01:33:34.849 --> 01:33:37.943
Bill, Bill, Bill.

01:34:03.478 --> 01:34:05.469
I'm sorry.

01:34:09.250 --> 01:34:10.717
Michael.

01:34:10.918 --> 01:34:15.082
The note you wrote her,
it's in your pocket.

01:34:29.504 --> 01:34:32.166
Forever and ever, babe.

01:34:38.880 --> 01:34:40.347
It's time to go.

01:35:15.383 --> 01:35:19.479
- Where am I?
- You're in Bed Bath & Beyond, sir.

01:35:19.687 --> 01:35:21.177
I was just watching you sleep.

01:35:21.389 --> 01:35:23.789
You looked like you were having
a crazy dream.

01:35:23.991 --> 01:35:24.958
What?

01:35:25.159 --> 01:35:28.822
You're not supposed to lay
in the beds, but I do sometimes.

01:35:31.799 --> 01:35:33.994
